# Aurora Light & Dark UI Redesign Plan

The user wants to continue applying the Aurora Light and Dark UI redesign. The previous implementation focused mainly on the Light mode foundation. We will now enhance both modes, ensuring a consistent and premium "Aurora" experience across the application, especially in Dark Mode.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Global CSS & Design System — [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/index.css)
Enhance [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/index.css) to provide rich dark mode variants for the Aurora theme.

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/index.css)
- **Backgrounds**: `body.dark` should use a deep, rich slate (`#0B1121` or `bg-slate-950`).
- **Cards**: Add `.dark .card` with deep backgrounds (`bg-slate-900`) and subtle glow borders (`border-slate-800`).
- **Aurora Blobs**: Add `.dark .aurora-blob-X` overrides to adjust opacity and mix-blend-mode for dark environments (e.g. `mix-blend-mode: screen`, slightly higher opacity for visibility against dark backgrounds).
- **Sidebar Links**: Ensure `.dark .sidebar-link-active` has a suitable dark gradient/glow background.
- **Buttons / Inputs**: Refine dark mode input focus rings and secondary button colors.

### 2. Layout Wrapper — [Layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/components/Layout.tsx)
Ensure the main layout correctly transitions between light and dark modes.

#### [MODIFY] [Layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/components/Layout.tsx)
- Add `dark:bg-slate-950` to the main container.
- Ensure the aurora blobs remain visible and active.

### 3. Sidebar — [Sidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/components/Sidebar.tsx)
Apply dark mode Aurora styling to the Sidebar.

#### [MODIFY] [Sidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/components/Sidebar.tsx)
- **Container**: Use `dark:bg-slate-900 dark:border-slate-800`.
- **Active Links**: Adjust active link styles so they look great in dark mode (e.g., `dark:bg-primary-900/20 dark:text-primary-400`).
- **Hover States**: Ensure hover states use `dark:hover:bg-slate-800`.
- **Dividers**: Use `dark:border-slate-800`.

### 4. Header — [Header.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/components/Header.tsx)
Apply dark mode glassmorphism and refined styles to the Header.

#### [MODIFY] [Header.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/components/Header.tsx)
- **Container**: Use `dark:bg-slate-950/80` for a sleek dark glass effect.
- **Search Bar**: Deep dark input `dark:bg-slate-900` with focus states.
- **Dropdowns**: Notifications and User dropdowns need `dark:bg-slate-900` and `dark:border-slate-800`.
- **Text & Icons**: Ensure icons and texts are `dark:text-slate-300` or `dark:text-slate-100`.

## Phase 2: Refinements & Remaining Pages

### 5. Dark Mode Card Hover Highlight
Enhance the `.dark .card-aurora:hover` state in [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/index.css) to add a subtle glowing border effect using an inset box-shadow or similar technique, per user request for more visible hover effects in dark mode.

### 6. Vehicles Page Table Layout Shift Fix
The HTML `<table>` auto-adjusts column widths when data loads, causing a layout shift.
We will apply `table-fixed` and specific width percentages/classes to `th` elements in [Vehicles.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/pages/Vehicles.tsx) to lock the layout.

### 7. Remaining Pages
Apply the `.card-aurora`, `page-fade-in`, and `stagger-X` classes to:
- Notifications ([Notifications.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/pages/Notifications.tsx))
- Vehicle forms/details ([VehicleForm.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/pages/VehicleForm.tsx), [VehicleDetail.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/pages/VehicleDetail.tsx))
