## Phase 5: Activity Logs feature with Undo Capability

The user has requested an ambitious feature to track every action in the application to a dedicated Activity Logs page. This includes creates, updates, deletes, and exports. Crucially, the system must allow administrators to "Undo" modifications and deletions. The page must adopt the Aurora theme.

### 11. Backend Models and Storage
Create a new MongoDB Mongoose schema to store activity.

#### [NEW] `backend/src/models/ActivityLog.ts`
- **Fields**: `userId` (ref User), [action](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/pages/Reports.tsx#162-166) (e.g. CREATE, UPDATE, DELETE, EXPORT), `resourceType` (e.g. Vehicle, Maintenance, AlertRule), `resourceId` (String), `description` (Human readable), `previousState` (Object, storing the exact document state before a change/deletion for restoration), `newState` (Object).

### 12. Backend Activity Logic and Undo Handler
Create the API to serve logs and process 'Undo' actions.

#### [NEW] `backend/src/controllers/logController.ts`
- `getLogs`: Fetch logs sorted by latest, with pagination.
- `undoAction`: Look at a specific log entry and reverse it. If it was a DELETE, re-insert the `previousState` document. If it was an UPDATE, replace the current document with the `previousState`.

#### [NEW] `backend/src/routes/logRoutes.ts`
- Expose `GET /` and `POST /:id/undo` protected by Admin auth.

#### [MODIFY] `backend/src/server.ts`
- Wire up the new `/api/logs` route.

### 13. Logging Integration across Controllers
Inject the logging utility into every major mutating controller method.

#### [MODIFY] `backend/src/controllers/*.ts`
- Update `vehicleController`, `maintenanceController`, `alertRuleController`, `userController`, and `reportController`.
- Before a document is updated or deleted, fetch its current state and pass it as `previousState` to the `ActivityLog` creation utility.
- Log exports explicitly in `reportController`.

### 14. Frontend API and State Management
Bind the new APIs into the frontend application.

#### [MODIFY] [api.ts](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/services/api.ts)
- Add `logApi.getAll()` and `logApi.undo()`.

#### [NEW] `frontend/src/store/slices/logSlice.ts`
- Handle fetching, pagination, and undo states. Add to `store/index.ts`.

### 15. Frontend Page & UI Construction
Construct the Aurora-themed timeline/list page.

#### [NEW] `frontend/src/pages/ActivityLogs.tsx`
- A beautiful chronological timeline or table of events.
- Distinct icons/colors for Creates (Green/Emerald), Updates (Blue/Cyan), Deletes (Red/Rose), Exports (Purple/Violet).
- Provide a clear "Undo" button on Delete/Update actions that calls the backend.
- Apply `card-aurora` and glassmorphic designs.

#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/App.tsx)
- Embed route `<Route path="logs" element={<ActivityLogs />} />` under the Admin area.

#### [MODIFY] [Sidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/components/Sidebar.tsx)
- Add navigation link to `/logs` with an appropriate icon (e.g., `History` or [Activity](file:///c:/Users/Anis/Documents/Web%20Pages/Fleet%20project/fleet-management-app/frontend/src/services/api.ts#288-290)).

## Verification Plan

### Automated
- Run `npm run build` to verify no TS errors.
- Ensure backend API calls work normally by browsing.

### Manual
- Navigate through all modified pages.
- Verify dark mode hover borders.
- Check Vehicles page for any remaining lag/layout shift upon load.
- Perform a create, update, delete, and export action. Verify they appear in `/logs`.
- Click 'Undo' on a deletion and verify the resource returns.
